&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Nabis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nabis is the #1 Licensed Cannabis Wholesale Platform in the world with the largest portfolio of cannabis brands, supplying hundreds of brands to retailers across California, New York, and Nevada. Our mission is to empower the world to discover cannabis by providing choice, access, and innovation.&amp;nbsp;We’re at the forefront of this movement and are building an innovative technology-first platform to scale the entirety of the cannabis industry. Through dedication to enhancing efficiency, transparency, and customer satisfaction, Nabis is paving the way for sweeping legalization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team, backed by Y Combinator and from a celebrity roster of tech luminaries and celebrities, including Doordash co-founder Stanley Tang, NFL Hall of Famer Joe Montana, Gmail creator Paul Buchheit, and Twitch cofounder Justin Kan, is scaling the cannabis supply chain with technology and our ultimate goal is to become the largest distributor of cannabis products in the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CashOps Confirmation Associate is responsible for verifying and confirming delivery and payment evidence submitted by drivers, ensuring all Cash on Demand (COD) and Must Pay Previous Balance (MPPB) orders are properly documented, compliant with SOP requirements, and ready for downstream processing. This role plays a critical control function in maintaining payment accuracy, visibility, and audit readiness across all hubs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payment Confirmation &amp;amp; Evidence Review&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review prior-day delivery evidence for all COD and MPPB orders to confirm payment collection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify required documentation is present and complete, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Signed delivery manifests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Signed METRC documents (where applicable)&lt;br&gt;Payment confirmation sheets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check images or ACH confirmations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure payment evidence is captured at the retailer location in accordance with SOP standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm delivery completion and payment status within internal systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee driver cash intake, payment bag verification, and chain-of-custody controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discrepancy Identification &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify missing, incomplete, or incorrect payment evidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log missing evidence or issues in the Driver Tracker Log.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate unresolved issues to the Cash Operations Sr. Associate with clear documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add notes and context to ensure visibility for Dispatch, Operations, and Accounting teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System &amp;amp; Process Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate delivery and payment status in internal tools (e.g., Nabis Admin, Retool).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure paid orders are processed within 48 hours of receiving them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records to support audits and compliance reviews.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–2 years of experience in cash handling, accounting support, operations, or audit-related roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and ability to identify inconsistencies in documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with SOP-driven environments and compliance controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working across Slack, internal systems, and shared logs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage time-sensitive reviews with minimal supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Nabis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nabis is the #1 licensed wholesale platform in the world with the largest portfolio of brands, supplying $1B+ worth of products per year from hundreds of brands to retailers across California, New York, and Nevada. Our mission is to empower the world to discover by providing choice, access, and innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re at the forefront of this movement and are building an innovative technology-first platform to scale the entirety of the industry. Through dedication to enhancing efficiency, transparency, and customer satisfaction, Nabis is paving the way for sweeping legalization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team, backed by Y Combinator and from a celebrity roster of tech luminaries and celebrities, including DoorDash co-founder Stanley Tang, NFL Hall of Famer Joe Montana, Gmail creator Paul Buchheit, and Twitch co-founder Justin Kan, is scaling the supply chain with technology, and our ultimate goal is to become the largest distributor of products in the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a reliable, professional Class A CDL Driver to support pickup and hub transfer routes across our New York locations. You&#39;ll be a critical part of our supply chain — keeping product moving safely, on time, and in compliance. &lt;strong&gt;1,000 sign-on bonus!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Run routes between our Rochester hub and NY brand locations, with day hauls to other Nabis hubs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Overnight stays in the Bronx Monday–Thursday (DOT-compliant scheduling)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Conduct pre- and post-trip safety inspections in line with company SOPs and OSHA standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Secure cargo using chains and binders; re-verify load stability throughout trips&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Inspect trailers for air line and jack position status before and after loading&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Visit weigh stations as required and adjust loads to meet state safety regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Assist with unloading at understaffed delivery sites while maintaining product integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Keep fleet vehicles clean, secure, and flagged for any maintenance needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Navigate routes via GPS; communicate with dispatch via CB radio and cab computer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Maintain professional communication with warehouse teams and dispatch at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Valid Class A CDL with 2+ years of occupational driving experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Airbrake endorsement required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Nabis&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nabis is the #1 licensed cannabis wholesale platform in the world, supplying $1B+ worth of cannabis products annually from hundreds of brands to retailers across California, New York, and Nevada. Our mission is to empower the world to discover cannabis by providing choice, access, and innovation.Through modern, scalable infrastructure, our mission is to empower the world to discover cannabis by providing choice, access, and innovation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re at the forefront of this movement, building an innovative, technology-first platform to scale the entire cannabis industry. Backed by Y Combinator and investors, including DoorDash Co-Founder Stanley Tang, NFL Hall of Famer Joe Montana, Gmail creator Paul Buchheit, and Twitch co-founder Justin Kan, Nabis is rapidly expanding across the U.S. with the goal of becoming the largest and most influential cannabis distribution network globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Nabis is seeking a qualified Class B CDL Warehouse Driver to run pickup routes to brands as well as routes between Nabis hubs. This person must have at least 2 years of experience as a reputable, trustworthy driver and be able to communicate in a timely and professional manner with our Nabis dispatch and warehouse teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation &amp;amp; Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay starting at &lt;strong&gt;$25&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;per hour, paid&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;weekly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll work at the fastest growing cannabis startup&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical/Dental/Vision offered to all full-time employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-rounded co-workers and teammates that are all striving towards the same goal. Nabis maintains a fun and energetic culture!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive routes to and from our Rochester hub to receive product from brands while supporting adhoc hauls to our other New York locations using medium fleet vehicles as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding problem solving and time management abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain fleet vehicles by keeping them clean and ensuring they are empty and secure when returned as well as flag any potential maintenance issues to our Fleet Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform regular safety inspections of equipment in keeping with company SOPs and OSHA standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow and maintain loading protocols, using chains and binders to secure cargo and re-checking their stability throughout trips&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect trailers before and after loading, paying attention to status of air lines and jack positions and adjusting them as necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visit weigh stations before and after packing to ensure that loads meet state safety regulations, making alterations to loads when required by law&lt;/li&gt;
